(43, 21, 6, 40, 7, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Obedience and Consequences', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience leading to results. In John 21:6, the disciples'' obedience to cast the net results in a great catch, while in Matthew 7:27, disobedience leads to the house''s fall.', 'theme', 0.286, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 7, 43, 13, 23, 23, 'whom Jesus loved', 'Connection of Beloved Disciple', 'This connection highlights the identity of the disciple whom Jesus loved, linking him to both passages. In John 21:7, this disciple recognizes Jesus, while in John 13:23, he is described as being close to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 7, 40, 14, 28, 29, 'It is the Lord', 'Peter''s Response to Jesus', 'This connection highlights Peter''s immediate reaction to Jesus in both passages. In John, Peter jumps into the sea upon recognizing the Lord, while in Matthew, he steps out of the boat to walk towards Him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 7, 43, 19, 26, 26, NULL, 'Connection of Beloved Disciple', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the disciple whom He loved. In John 21:7, this disciple identifies Jesus, while in John 19:26, he is present at the crucifixion, highlighting his significance in Jesus'' life.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 7, 47, 5, 14, 14, 'It is the Lord', 'Love and Response to Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of love and action in response to Christ. In John 21:7, the beloved disciple recognizes Jesus, prompting Peter''s immediate response, while in 2 Corinthians 5:14, the love of Christ compels believers to act.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 7, 19, 118, 23, 23, 'It is the Lord', 'Recognition of the Lord''s Presence', 'This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus as Lord in John 21:7, which parallels the acknowledgment of God''s marvelous works in Psalms 118:23. Both passages emphasize the significance of recognizing divine action.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 7, 22, 8, 7, 7, 'It is the Lord', 'Connection of Love and Recognition', 'This connection highlights the theme of love''s power and recognition. In John 21:7, Peter''s immediate response to recognize Jesus reflects a deep love, while Song of Solomon 8:7 emphasizes that love cannot be quenched or drowned by any force.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 7, 41, 11, 3, 3, 'It is the Lord', 'Recognition of the Lord''s Authority', 'This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus as ''the Lord'' in both passages. In John 21:7, Peter acknowledges Jesus'' presence, while in Mark 11:3, the authority of the Lord is invoked for action.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 8, 5, 3, 11, 11, 'cubits', 'Measurement and Scale in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the use of cubits as a unit of measurement in both passages. John 21:8 mentions ''two hundred cubits,'' while Deuteronomy 3:11 specifies ''nine cubits,'' emphasizing a shared cultural context of measurement.', 'keyword', 0.265, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 9, 11, 19, 5, 6, 'fire of coals', 'Provision and Nourishment', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine provision in both passages. In John 21:9, the disciples find fish and bread, while in 1 Kings 19:5-6, Elijah is provided with a cake baked on coals, emphasizing God''s care for His followers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 9, 43, 21, 10, 10, 'fish laid thereon', 'Connection of Fish and Bread', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of fish, with the first noting fish laid on the fire and the second inviting the disciples to bring their catch. This connection highlights the significance of the fish in the context of Jesus'' provision and the disciples'' efforts.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 9, 43, 18, 18, 18, 'fire of coals', 'Connection of Coals and Fire', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of a ''fire of coals.'' In John 18:18, Peter warms himself by this fire, while in John 21:9, a similar fire is used to prepare food, linking moments of warmth and sustenance in Peter''s journey.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 9, 40, 4, 11, 11, NULL, 'Divine Provision and Care', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine provision, as both passages depict moments of sustenance and care. In John 21:9, the disciples find fish and bread prepared for them, while in Matthew 4:11, angels minister to Jesus, providing for his needs.', 'theme', 0.3, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 9, 41, 8, 3, 3, 'fish laid thereon, and bread', 'Connection of Provision and Need', 'This connection highlights the theme of provision in both passages. In John 21:9, the presence of fish and bread signifies sustenance, while Mark 8:3 addresses the need for food for those who have traveled far.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 9, 42, 12, 29, 31, 'fish laid thereon, and bread', 'Provision and Trust in God', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s provision for physical needs. In John 21:9, the disciples find fish and bread, while Luke 12:29-31 encourages believers not to worry about food and drink, assuring them that God knows their needs.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 11, 42, 5, 6, 8, NULL, 'Miraculous Catch of Fish', 'Both passages emphasize a miraculous catch of fish, highlighting the abundance of fish caught. In John, the net is not broken, while in Luke, the net breaks, illustrating different outcomes of divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 11, 44, 2, 41, 41, 'great fishes', 'Connection of Abundance and Growth', 'This connection highlights the theme of abundance in both passages. In John 21:11, the net holds ''great fishes,'' while in Acts 2:41, ''about three thousand souls'' are added, illustrating a miraculous growth.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 12, 44, 10, 41, 41, NULL, 'Eating with the Resurrected Christ', 'This connection highlights the shared experience of the disciples who ''did eat and drink with him'' after his resurrection. Both passages emphasize the intimate fellowship with Jesus post-resurrection, reinforcing the reality of his physical presence.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 12, 42, 9, 45, 45, 'durst ask him, Who art thou?', 'Understanding and Fear of Asking', 'This connection highlights the disciples'' hesitation to inquire further about Jesus'' identity and teachings. Both passages emphasize a sense of fear and uncertainty in approaching Jesus, leading to a lack of understanding.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 12, 43, 16, 19, 19, 'Who art thou?', 'Disciples'' Inquiry and Recognition', 'This connection highlights the disciples'' desire to understand Jesus'' identity and teachings. In both passages, there is an emphasis on the disciples'' unasked questions and their recognition of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
